uot;If they have a blade through their throat, they cannot see you&quot; school of stealth.  Hey, whatever works.  So off we go, warrior tanking and rogue backstabbing, leaving a trail of bleeding corpses in our wake.  We don't stand I chance I think... then I notice she can pull one enemy at a time... no wonder she can solo in Solusek A, of all places.  Once, she pulls a pair of solusek champions... we're doomed I think... then one falls over.  Her life is droping, the second one has a damage shield as well, we're both burning... she's at a bubble of health, half a bubble, a quarter bubble, and eigth... and down falls the goblin.  &quot;Hmm... 38 hitpoints&quot; she muses.  Yesh.<br>
  Five minutes later, both of us looking like mummies from all the bandages, we proceed into the room... and realize that just behind the door is Lynada the exiled, with her earth pet in tow, plus a champion and high priest to boot.  Well at least we got this far, I think, and sit down to rest...<br>
  &quot;Well, it would take too long to heal!&quot; she cries, drawing her bow.  Quick as I can I apply my putrid bane poison I've been saving for Lynada... but fail in the attempt.  Too late, I hear the arrow fly... and out comes the exiled.   Blinking, I look up to see spells flying in my face, and she's on me already.  The dark one.  I launch at her with my blade, and reach for the purse she carries.  Batting away my hand, her blade aims for me...<br>
  I confess I blanked out.  I awoke in High keep, confussed... remebering her screaming something about an inability to drop... yet when I ran back to Solusek's Eye there she was, and with a the sparkle purse, which she had gotten before she too was stricken.<br>
  And now I have a burning rapier! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uveloxiavoluptuous.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Veloxia Voluptuous</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 229<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/26/02 6:09:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=138.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The story</span><hr size=1> *blushes* oh you play me up too much! lol<br>
